#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:5
msgid "Admissions (CRM pipeline)"
msgstr "Les admissions (pipeline CRM)"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:8
msgid ""
"Manage nursing home (MR/MRS) admissions with Resthome: a CRM pipeline from "
"first contact to admission, plus a wizard that creates the resident and "
"stay."
msgstr ""
"Gérer les admissions en maison de repos (MR/MRS) avec Resthome : pipeline "
"CRM du premier contact à l'admission, assistant qui crée le résident et le "
"séjour."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:12
msgid "Where is the admissions pipeline in Resthome?"
msgstr "Où se trouve le pipeline des admissions dans Resthome ?"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:13
msgid ""
"In the CRM app, select the \"Admissions\" team. The pipeline shows "
"prospective residents in a kanban view, from first contact through to "
"admission."
msgstr ""
"Dans l'application CRM, sélectionnez l'équipe « Admissions ». Le pipeline y "
"affiche les candidats résidents en kanban, du premier contact jusqu'à "
"l'admission."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:15
msgid "How do I turn a prospect into a resident?"
msgstr "Comment transformer un candidat en résident ?"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:16
msgid ""
"Move the lead to the \"Admitted\" stage (or click the Won button). A wizard "
"opens: pick the room and the stay start date, then confirm. Resthome then "
"creates the contact as a resident and opens their stay."
msgstr ""
"Déplacez la piste vers l'étape « Admis » (ou cliquez sur le bouton Gagné). "
"Un assistant s'ouvre : choisissez la chambre et la date de début de séjour, "
"puis validez. Resthome crée alors le contact comme résident et ouvre son "
"séjour."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:18
msgid "Is a room required to admit a prospect?"
msgstr "La chambre est-elle obligatoire pour admettre un candidat ?"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:19
msgid ""
"Yes. The admission wizard requires an available room and a stay start date; "
"without a room, the admission cannot be finalized."
msgstr ""
"Oui. L'assistant d'admission exige une chambre disponible et une date de "
"début de séjour ; sans chambre, l'admission ne peut pas être finalisée."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:21
msgid "What happens if I move a lead out of the \"Admitted\" stage?"
msgstr "Que se passe-t-il si je sors une piste de l'étape « Admis » ?"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:22
msgid ""
"Resthome automatically cancels any draft or confirmed stays linked to that "
"lead. A stay that has already started (active) is left untouched."
msgstr ""
"Resthome annule automatiquement les séjours encore en brouillon ou confirmés"
" rattachés à cette piste. Un séjour déjà démarré (actif) n'est pas touché."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:24
msgid "Do I need to check insurability before admitting?"
msgstr "Faut-il vérifier l'assurabilité avant d'admettre ?"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:25
msgid ""
"Yes, except in specific cases. Until the MDA check has succeeded, moving to "
"\"Admitted\" is blocked. You can uncheck \"MDA check required\" for cases "
"without a NISS (a foreign resident, for example)."
msgstr ""
"Oui, sauf cas particulier. Tant que la vérification MDA n'a pas réussi, le "
"passage à « Admis » est bloqué. Vous pouvez décocher « Contrôle MDA requis »"
" pour les cas sans NISS (résident étranger, par exemple)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:27
msgid ""
"What is the difference between the stay start date and the admission date?"
msgstr ""
"Quelle différence entre la date de début de séjour et la date d'admission ?"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:28
msgid ""
"The stay start date triggers billing for accommodation (the room); the "
"admission date marks the start of the health insurer's contribution and is "
"set when the stay is started. They are often identical, but can differ."
msgstr ""
"La date de début de séjour lance la facturation de l'hébergement (la "
"chambre) ; la date d'admission correspond au début de l'intervention de la "
"mutuelle et se fixe au démarrage du séjour. Elles sont souvent identiques, "
"mais peuvent différer."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:31
msgid ""
"The **admission pipeline** is the entry point of a resident's journey. It "
"lets you track every **prospect** — from a relative's first enquiry through "
"to the actual move-in — and then, in a single action, **turn them into a "
"resident** with their room and stay."
msgstr ""
"Le **pipeline d'admission** est le point d'entrée du parcours d'un résident."
" Il vous permet de suivre chaque **candidat** — de la première demande d'un "
"proche jusqu'à l'entrée effective — puis, en un geste, de le **transformer "
"en résident** avec sa chambre et son séjour."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:36
msgid ""
"You will find it in the **CRM** app, under the **Admissions** team. Each "
"enquiry becomes a **lead** (a prospective resident) that you move from stage"
" to stage on a kanban board."
msgstr ""
"Vous le trouvez dans l'application **CRM**, sur l'équipe **Admissions**. "
"Chaque demande y devient une **piste** (un candidat résident) que vous "
"faites progresser d'étape en étape dans un tableau kanban."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:40
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Vue d'ensemble"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:51
msgid "Two dates not to confuse"
msgstr "Deux dates à ne pas confondre"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:54
msgid ""
"**Stay start date**: when billing for accommodation (the room) begins. This "
"is the one you enter in the admission wizard."
msgstr ""
"**Date de début de séjour** : quand commence la facturation de l'hébergement"
" (la chambre). C'est celle que vous saisissez dans l'assistant d'admission."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:56
msgid ""
"**Admission date**: when the health insurer's contribution (the dependency "
"allowance) begins. It is set later, when the **stay is started**."
msgstr ""
"**Date d'admission** : quand commence l'intervention de la mutuelle (le "
"forfait de dépendance). Elle se fixe plus tard, au **démarrage du séjour**."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:59
msgid "They are often identical, but can differ."
msgstr "Elles sont souvent identiques, mais peuvent différer."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:62
msgid "1. Open the Admissions pipeline"
msgstr "1\\. Ouvrir le pipeline Admissions"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:64
msgid "Open the **CRM** app."
msgstr "Ouvrez l'application **CRM**."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:65
msgid ""
"Select the **Admissions** team / pipeline (menu **Sales → My Pipeline**, "
"then filter on the Admissions team, or open the team directly from the teams"
" view)."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez l'équipe / le pipeline **Admissions** (menu **Ventes → Mon "
"pipeline**, puis filtrez sur l'équipe Admissions, ou ouvrez directement "
"l'équipe depuis la vue des équipes)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:67
msgid ""
"The **kanban** board shows one column per stage and one card per prospect."
msgstr ""
"Le tableau **kanban** affiche une colonne par étape et une carte par "
"candidat."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:69
msgid ""
"![Admissions pipeline in kanban view, one column per stage from First "
"contact to Admitted](../assets/screenshots/residents/01-pipeline-"
"admissions.webp)"
msgstr ""
"![Pipeline des admissions en vue kanban, une colonne par étape, de Premier "
"contact à Admis](../assets/screenshots/residents/01-pipeline-"
"admissions.webp)"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:69
msgid ""
"Admissions pipeline in kanban view, one column per stage from First contact "
"to Admitted"
msgstr ""
"Pipeline des admissions en vue kanban, une colonne par étape, de Premier "
"contact à Admis"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:71
msgid "2. Create an admission lead"
msgstr "2\\. Créer une piste d'admission"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:73
msgid "Click **New**."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **Nouveau**."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:74
msgid "Give the lead a **name** (for example \"Admission - Prospect name\")."
msgstr ""
"Donnez un **nom** à la piste (par exemple « Admission - Nom du candidat »)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:75
msgid ""
"The **Prospective resident** checkbox is ticked automatically when the lead "
"belongs to the Admissions team. It enables the **Resident admission** tab "
"and hides the sales sections (company, marketing) that are not needed here."
msgstr ""
"La case **Candidat résident** est cochée automatiquement lorsque la piste "
"appartient à l'équipe Admissions. Elle active l'onglet **Admission "
"résident** et masque les sections commerciales (société, marketing) inutiles"
" ici."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:78
msgid "**Save.**"
msgstr "**Enregistrez.**"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:80
msgid "The prospect and the relative who calls"
msgstr "Le candidat et le proche qui appelle"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:83
msgid ""
"Often it is a **relative** (a son or daughter) who makes contact on behalf "
"of the person to be accommodated. Resthome keeps the two apart: the "
"**prospective resident** is the person being accommodated, while the caller "
"is recorded as a **family contact**. At admission, the identity (NISS, date "
"of birth) is carried by the resident, not the relative."
msgstr ""
"Souvent, c'est un **proche** (fils, fille) qui prend contact pour la "
"personne à héberger. Resthome distingue les deux : le **candidat résident** "
"est la personne hébergée, tandis que l'appelant est enregistré comme "
"**contact familial**. À l'admission, l'identité (NISS, date de naissance) "
"est portée par le résident, pas par le proche."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:90
msgid "The \"Resident admission\" tab"
msgstr "L'onglet « Admission résident »"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:92
msgid "This is where you build the prospect's file without leaving the lead:"
msgstr ""
"C'est ici que vous constituez le dossier du candidat, sans quitter la piste "
":"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:94
msgid ""
"**Personal information**: NISS, date of birth, gender, attending physician, "
"family contacts, and above all the **requested stay type** (MR, MRS or short"
" stay)."
msgstr ""
"**Informations personnelles** : NISS, date de naissance, genre, médecin "
"traitant, contacts familiaux, et surtout le **type de séjour souhaité** (MR,"
" MRS ou court séjour)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:97
msgid ""
"**Health insurer / Insurability**: health insurer, insurance scheme, "
"affiliation code, and the result of the **MDA check** (CT1/CT2, BIM status)."
msgstr ""
"**Mutuelle / Assurabilité** : mutuelle, régime d'assurance, code "
"d'affiliation, et le résultat de la **vérification MDA** (CT1/CT2, statut "
"BIM)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "Short stay (short stay / CSJ)"
msgstr "Court séjour (court séjour / CSJ)"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:103
msgid ""
"If you choose **short stay**, two additional fields appear: the **number of "
"short-stay days already used** this calendar year and **notes**. The law "
"caps short stays at **90 days per year**; fill in this information (ask the "
"family, or confirm by phone with the health insurer) before accepting the "
"admission."
msgstr ""
"Si vous choisissez **court séjour**, deux champs supplémentaires "
"apparaissent : le **nombre de jours de court séjour déjà utilisés** cette "
"année civile et des **notes**. La loi limite le court séjour à **90 jours "
"par an** ; renseignez l'information (demandez à la famille, ou confirmez par"
" téléphone avec la mutuelle) avant d'accepter l'admission."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:109
msgid ""
"![Resident admission tab of a lead, with the Personal information and Health"
" insurer / Insurability blocks](../assets/screenshots/residents/02-lead-"
"admission-resident.webp)"
msgstr ""
"![Onglet Admission résident d'une piste, avec les blocs Informations "
"personnelles et Mutuelle / "
"Assurabilité](../assets/screenshots/residents/02-lead-admission-"
"resident.webp)"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:109
msgid ""
"Resident admission tab of a lead, with the Personal information and Health "
"insurer / Insurability blocks"
msgstr ""
"Onglet Admission résident d'une piste, avec les blocs Informations "
"personnelles et Mutuelle / Assurabilité"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:111
msgid "3. Move the lead forward"
msgstr "3\\. Faire avancer la piste"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:113
msgid ""
"Drag the card from one column to the next, at the actual pace of the case:"
msgstr ""
"Faites glisser la carte d'une colonne à l'autre, au rythme réel du dossier :"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "Stage"
msgstr "Étape"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "Meaning"
msgstr "Signification"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "**First contact**"
msgstr "**Premier contact**"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "Enquiry received, to be followed up."
msgstr "Demande reçue, à recontacter."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "**Visit scheduled**"
msgstr "**Visite planifiée**"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "A visit to the facility has been booked."
msgstr "Une visite de l'établissement est fixée."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "**Visit done**"
msgstr "**Visite effectuée**"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "The visit has taken place."
msgstr "La visite a eu lieu."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "**File complete**"
msgstr "**Dossier complet**"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "The administrative and medical file is ready."
msgstr "Le dossier administratif et médical est prêt."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "**Admitted**"
msgstr "**Admis**"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "The \"won\" stage: triggers the admission wizard."
msgstr "Étape « gagnée » : déclenche l'assistant d'admission."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "**Refused / Withdrawn**"
msgstr "**Refusé / Désisté**"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:100
msgid "The enquiry does not go ahead (folded column)."
msgstr "La demande n'aboutit pas (colonne repliée)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:124
msgid ""
"You can also schedule visit appointments directly from the lead "
"(**Meetings** button / shared calendar)."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez aussi planifier les rendez-vous de visite directement depuis la "
"piste (bouton **Réunions** / calendrier partagé)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:127
msgid "4. Check insurability (MDA)"
msgstr "4\\. Vérifier l'assurabilité (MDA)"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:129
msgid ""
"Before you can admit the prospect, check that they are properly insured:"
msgstr ""
"Avant de pouvoir admettre le candidat, vérifiez qu'il est bien assuré :"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:131
msgid "On the lead, click **Check insurability** (header)."
msgstr "Sur la piste, cliquez sur **Vérifier l'assurabilité** (en-tête)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:132
msgid ""
"Resthome sends an **MDA** request (MyCareNet / WalCareNet insurability) and "
"automatically updates the prospect's **health insurer**, **BIM** status and "
"**CT1/CT2** codes."
msgstr ""
"Resthome envoie une requête **MDA** (assurabilité MyCareNet / WalCareNet) et"
" met à jour automatiquement la **mutuelle**, le statut **BIM** et les codes "
"**CT1/CT2** du candidat."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:136
msgid "The MDA check gates admission"
msgstr "Le contrôle MDA conditionne l'admission"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:139
msgid ""
"Until the MDA check has **succeeded**, moving to the **Admitted** stage is "
"**blocked**. For a case without a NISS (a foreign resident, a newborn, "
"etc.), uncheck **MDA check required** in the Resident admission tab to "
"remove the block. If the MDA comes back as **not insured**, admission is "
"still possible but Resthome warns you: billing will then have to be "
"addressed to the resident, not to the health insurer."
msgstr ""
"Tant que la vérification MDA n'a pas **réussi**, le passage à l'étape "
"**Admis** est **bloqué**. Pour un cas sans NISS (résident étranger, nouveau-"
"né…), décochez **Contrôle MDA requis** dans l'onglet Admission résident pour"
" lever le blocage. Si le MDA revient **non assuré**, l'admission reste "
"possible mais Resthome vous avertit : la facturation devra alors être "
"adressée au résident, pas à la mutuelle."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:147
msgid ""
"For a full understanding of the insurability check, see [Insurability "
"(MDA)](../ehealth/mda.md)."
msgstr ""
"Pour tout comprendre du contrôle d'assurabilité, voir [Assurabilité "
"(MDA)](../ehealth/mda.md)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:150
msgid "5. Admit the prospect"
msgstr "5\\. Admettre le candidat"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:152
msgid ""
"When the file is ready, turn the prospect into a resident. Two equivalent "
"actions open the **admission wizard**:"
msgstr ""
"Quand le dossier est prêt, transformez le candidat en résident. Deux gestes "
"équivalents ouvrent l'**assistant d'admission** :"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:155
msgid "**Drag** the card into the **Admitted** column, or"
msgstr "**Faire glisser** la carte dans la colonne **Admis**, ou"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:156
msgid "Open the lead and click the **Won** button."
msgstr "Ouvrir la piste et cliquer sur le bouton **Gagné**."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:158
msgid "Before marking as \"Admitted\""
msgstr "Avant de marquer « Admis »"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:161
msgid ""
"The **requested stay type** (MR / MRS / short stay) must be filled in: it "
"determines the bed and Annexe 7. The MDA check must also have succeeded (see"
" above). Otherwise, Resthome blocks the operation and tells you what to "
"complete."
msgstr ""
"Le **type de séjour souhaité** (MR / MRS / court séjour) doit être renseigné"
" : il détermine le lit et l'Annexe 7. Le contrôle MDA doit également être "
"réussi (voir ci-dessus). À défaut, Resthome bloque l'opération et vous "
"indique quoi compléter."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:166
msgid "The admission wizard asks you for:"
msgstr "L'assistant d'admission vous demande :"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:168
msgid "The **room** — **required**; only **available** rooms are offered."
msgstr ""
"La **chambre** — **obligatoire** ; seules les chambres **disponibles** sont "
"proposées."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:169
msgid ""
"The **stay type** — carried over from the prospect (MR / MRS / short stay), "
"read-only."
msgstr ""
"Le **type de séjour** — repris du candidat (MR / MRS / court séjour), en "
"lecture seule."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:171
msgid "The **stay start date** — defaults to today."
msgstr "La **date de début de séjour** — par défaut aujourd'hui."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:173
msgid "Click **Admit** to confirm."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **Admettre** pour valider."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:175
msgid ""
"![Admission wizard dialog showing the Name, Stay type, Room and Start date "
"fields, with the Admit button](../assets/screenshots/residents/03-assistant-"
"admission.webp)"
msgstr ""
"![Fenêtre de l'assistant d'admission avec les champs Nom, Type de séjour, "
"Chambre et Date d'entrée, et le bouton "
"Admettre](../assets/screenshots/residents/03-assistant-admission.webp)"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:175
msgid ""
"Admission wizard dialog showing the Name, Stay type, Room and Start date "
"fields, with the Admit button"
msgstr ""
"Fenêtre de l'assistant d'admission avec les champs Nom, Type de séjour, "
"Chambre et Date d'entrée, et le bouton Admettre"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:177
msgid "What the admission creates"
msgstr "Ce que l'admission crée"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:179
msgid "When you confirm the wizard, Resthome:"
msgstr "En validant l'assistant, Resthome :"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:181
msgid ""
"**creates the contact as a resident** (and removes them from the list of "
"prospective residents);"
msgstr ""
"**crée le contact comme résident** (et le retire de la liste des futurs "
"résidents) ;"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:183
msgid ""
"**opens the corresponding stay**, in the **Confirmed** state, on the chosen "
"room and date;"
msgstr ""
"**ouvre le séjour** correspondant, à l'état **Confirmé**, sur la chambre et "
"à la date choisies ;"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:185
msgid ""
"**opens the resident's record** so you can continue (Katz, documents, stay)."
msgstr ""
"**ouvre la fiche du résident** pour poursuivre (Katz, documents, séjour)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:187
msgid ""
"The stay then still needs to be **started** (**Start Stay** button) once the"
" resident is actually present — it is this start that sets the **admission "
"date** and triggers billing. See [Manage a resident](gerer-un-resident.md)."
msgstr ""
"Le séjour reste ensuite à **démarrer** (bouton **Start Stay**) quand le "
"résident est effectivement présent — c'est ce démarrage qui fixe la **date "
"d'admission** et déclenche la facturation. Voir [Gérer un résident](gerer-"
"un-resident.md)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:191
msgid "Safeguards and edge cases"
msgstr "Gardes-fous et cas particuliers"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:193
msgid "Resthome protects the consistency of the pipeline:"
msgstr "Resthome protège la cohérence du pipeline :"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:195
msgid ""
"**Wizard cancellation** — if you close the wizard without admitting, the "
"lead **returns to the previous stage**: nothing is created until you "
"confirm."
msgstr ""
"**Annulation de l'assistant** — si vous fermez l'assistant sans admettre, la"
" piste **revient à l'étape précédente** : rien n'est créé tant que vous "
"n'avez pas validé."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:197
msgid ""
"**Regression out of \"Admitted\"** — if you move an already-admitted lead "
"back to an earlier stage, Resthome **automatically cancels** the stays still"
" in **draft** or **confirmed** state linked to that lead. A stay that has "
"already been **started** (active) is left untouched."
msgstr ""
"**Régression hors « Admis »** — si vous ressortez une piste déjà admise vers"
" une étape antérieure, Resthome **annule automatiquement** les séjours "
"encore en **brouillon** ou **confirmés** rattachés à cette piste. Un séjour "
"déjà **démarré** (actif) n'est pas touché."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:201
msgid ""
"**Duplicate detection** — the admission is tied to the **resident**, not "
"just to the lead. If a stay already exists for this person, Resthome reuses "
"it rather than creating a second one; a confirmed stay belonging to "
"**another** lead is never \"stolen\"."
msgstr ""
"**Détection de doublon** — l'admission est rattachée au **résident**, pas "
"seulement à la piste. Si un séjour existe déjà pour cette personne, Resthome"
" le réutilise plutôt que d'en créer un second ; un séjour confirmé "
"appartenant à une **autre** piste n'est jamais « volé »."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:205
msgid ""
"**Re-dragging a lead** — if you reopen the wizard on a lead that already has"
" a stay, that stay's **room** is pre-filled."
msgstr ""
"**Re-glisser une piste** — si vous rouvrez l'assistant sur une piste qui a "
"déjà un séjour, la **chambre** de ce séjour est pré-remplie."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:208
msgid "Key takeaways"
msgstr "Points clés à retenir"

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:210
msgid ""
"The **Admissions** pipeline lives in the **CRM** app; each prospect is a "
"lead that you move forward on the kanban board."
msgstr ""
"Le pipeline **Admissions** vit dans l'application **CRM** ; chaque candidat "
"est une piste que vous faites progresser en kanban."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:212
msgid ""
"The **Resident admission** tab centralizes the prospect's identity, health "
"insurer and **MDA** check."
msgstr ""
"L'onglet **Admission résident** centralise l'identité, la mutuelle et le "
"contrôle **MDA** du candidat."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:214
msgid ""
"Moving to **Admitted** (drag-and-drop or the **Won** button) opens the "
"wizard: **room required** + **stay start date**, then creation of the "
"**resident** and the **stay**."
msgstr ""
"Le passage à **Admis** (glisser-déposer ou bouton **Gagné**) ouvre "
"l'assistant : **chambre obligatoire** + **date de début de séjour**, puis "
"création du **résident** et du **séjour**."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:217
msgid ""
"Admission is **blocked** without a stay type filled in and without a "
"**successful MDA** (unless the MDA check is unchecked)."
msgstr ""
"L'admission est **bloquée** sans type de séjour renseigné et sans **MDA "
"réussi** (sauf contrôle MDA décoché)."

#: ../../content/residents/admissions.md:219
msgid ""
"Moving a lead out of **Admitted** cancels its **draft/confirmed** stays; "
"**active** stays are preserved."
msgstr ""
"Sortir une piste de **Admis** annule ses séjours **brouillon/confirmés** ; "
"les séjours **actifs** sont préservés."

